      "variant": "main",
      "html": "<h4>Finding Intercepts from Graphs and Equations</h4>\n<section data-depth=\"1\" id=\"fs-id1167835400371\">\n<div class=\"be-prepared\" data-type=\"note\" id=\"fs-id1170654939047\">\n<div data-type=\"title\">\n<div data-type=\"title\">The points where a line crosses the \\( x \\)-axis and the \\( y \\)-axis are called the intercepts of the line.</div>\n<div data-type=\"title\"><span><br></span></div>\n<div data-type=\"title\"><span>Let&rsquo;s look at the graphs of the lines.</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<span data-alt=\"The figure shows four graphs of different equations. In example a the graph of 2 x plus y plus 6 is graphed on the x y-coordinate plane. The x and y axes run from negative 8 to 8. The points (0, 6) and (3, 0) are plotted and labeled. A straight line goes through both points and has arrows on both ends. In example b the graph of 3 x minus 4 y plus 12 is graphed on the x y-coordinate plane. The x and y axes run from negative 8 to 8. The points (0, negative 3) and (4, 0) are plotted and labeled. A straight line goes through both points and has arrows on both ends. In example c the graph of x minus y plus 5 is graphed on the x y-coordinate plane. The x and y axes run from negative 8 to 8. The points (0, negative 5) and (5, 0) are plotted and labeled. A straight line goes through both points and has arrows on both ends. In example d the graph of y plus negative 2 x is graphed on the x y-coordinate plane. The x and y axes run from negative 8 to 8. The point (0, 0) is plotted and labeled. A straight line goes through this point and the points (negative 1, 2) and (1, negative 2) and has arrows on both ends.\" data-type=\"media\" id=\"fs-id1167835343912\">\n<img alt=\"The figure shows four graphs of different equations. In example a the graph of 2 x plus y plus 6 is graphed on the x y-coordinate plane. The x and y axes run from negative 8 to 8. The points (0, 6) and (3, 0) are plotted and labeled. A straight line goes through both points and has arrows on both ends. In example b the graph of 3 x minus 4 y plus 12 is graphed on the x y-coordinate plane. The x and y axes run from negative 8 to 8. The points (0, negative 3) and (4, 0) are plotted and labeled. A straight line goes through both points and has arrows on both ends. In example c the graph of x minus y plus 5 is graphed on the x y-coordinate plane. The x and y axes run from negative 8 to 8. The points (0, negative 5) and (5, 0) are plotted and labeled. A straight line goes through both points and has arrows on both ends. In example d the graph of y plus negative 2 x is graphed on the x y-coordinate plane. The x and y axes run from negative 8 to 8. The point (0, 0) is plotted and labeled. A straight line goes through this point and the points (negative 1, 2) and (1, negative 2) and has arrows on both ends.\" class=\"img-fluid atto_image_button_text-bottom\" height=\"716\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/fe7c894af22fc816272cc2a3a72e056a1da78b83\" width=\"643\">\n</span>\n<p id=\"fs-id1167831887736\"><br></p>\n<p id=\"fs-id1167831887736\">First, notice where each of these lines crosses the <em data-effect=\"italics\">\\( x \\)</em>-axis.</p>\n<p id=\"fs-id1167835345975\">Now, let&rsquo;s look at the points where these lines cross the <em data-effect=\"italics\">\\( y \\)</em>-axis.</p>\n<table a and at: b c columns. contains crosses d fifth figure first for fourth has header headers id=\"fs-id1167835367746\" is line negative pair point row rows second sixth table the third this with x-axis y-axis>\n<thead>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<th data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"middle\"><span data-effect=\"bold\">Figure</span></th>\n<th data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"top\"><span data-effect=\"bold\">The line crosses<span data-type=\"newline\"><br></span>the <em data-effect=\"italics\">\\( x \\)</em>-axis at:</span></th>\n<th data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"top\"><span data-effect=\"bold\">Ordered pair<span data-type=\"newline\"><br></span>for this point</span></th>\n<th data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><span data-effect=\"bold\">The line crosses<span data-type=\"newline\"><br></span>the <em data-effect=\"italics\">\\( y \\)-</em>axis at:</span></th>\n<th data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><span data-effect=\"bold\">Ordered pair<span data-type=\"newline\"><br></span>for this poin</span><strong data-effect=\"bold\">t</strong></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\">Figure (a)</td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\">3</td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>3</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>3</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\">6</td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>6</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>6</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\">Figure (b)</td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\">4</td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>4</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>4</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>&minus;3</mn>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mn>&minus;3</mn>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>&minus;3</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>&minus;3</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\">Figure (c)</td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\">5</td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>5</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>5</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>&minus;5</mn>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mn>&minus;5</mn>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>5</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>5</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\">Figure (d)</td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\">0</td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\">0</td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\">General Figure</td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><em data-effect=\"italics\">a</em></td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mi>a</mi>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mi>a</mi>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><em data-effect=\"italics\">b</em></td>\n<td data-align=\"center\" data-valign=\"middle\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mi>b</mi>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0</mn>\n<mo>,</mo>\n<mi>b</mi>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p id=\"fs-id1167834535864\"><br></p>\n<p class=\"be-prepared\" id=\"fs-id1167834535861\"><strong>X-INTERCEPT and <i>Y</i></strong><span><strong>-INTERCEPT of a Line</strong></span></p>\n<p class=\"be-prepared\" id=\"fs-id1167834535861\"><span>The </span><em data-effect=\"italics\">x</em><span>-intercept is the point </span>\\( (a , 0) \\)<math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo><em data-effect=\"italics\"></em></mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math><span> where the line crosses the </span><em data-effect=\"italics\">x</em><span><span>-axis.</span><br>The y-intercept is the point \\( (0 , b) \\)<em data-effect=\"italics\"></em> where the line crosses the y-axis.<br><img alt=\"The table has 3 rows and 2 columns. The first row is a header row with the headers x and y. The second row contains a and 0. The third row contains 0 and b.\" class=\"img-fluid atto_image_button_text-bottom\" height=\"92\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/cfa22a98c89816890def2a20a309f5e74ebe366d\" width=\"429\"><br></span></p>\n<div data-type=\"example\" id=\"fs-id1167834300811\">\n<div data-type=\"exercise\" id=\"fs-id1167834300813\">\n<div data-type=\"problem\" id=\"fs-id1167834300815\">\n<p id=\"fs-id1167835376064\"><strong><br>Find the <em data-effect=\"italics\"><em data-effect=\"italics\"><em data-effect=\"italics\">\\( x \\)</em></em></em>- and <em data-effect=\"italics\"><em data-effect=\"italics\"><em data-effect=\"italics\">\\( y \\)</em></em></em>-intercepts from the Equation of a Line</strong><br></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"be-prepared\" data-type=\"note\" id=\"fs-id1170654939047\">\n<div data-type=\"title\">\n<div data-type=\"title\">\n<div data-type=\"title\"><span>Use the equation of the line. To find:</span><br></div>\n<div data-type=\"title\">\n<ul>\n<li><span>the x-intercept of the line, let&nbsp;\\( y = 0 \\) and solve for \\(&nbsp;x&nbsp;\\).</span></li>\n<li><span>the y-intercept of the line, let \\( x = 0 \\) and solve for \\(&nbsp;y&nbsp;\\).</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div data-type=\"note\" id=\"fs-id1167835410566\">\n<ul data-bullet-style=\"bullet\" id=\"fs-id1167834246665\">\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div data-type=\"example\" id=\"fs-id1167827987818\">\n<div data-type=\"exercise\" id=\"fs-id1167827987820\">\n<div data-type=\"problem\" id=\"fs-id1167827987822\">\n<p id=\"fs-id1167827987825\"><strong>Example</strong><br><br>Find the intercepts of \\( 2x + y = 8 \\)<math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<semantics>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mo></mo>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</math></p>\n</div>\n<div data-type=\"solution\" id=\"fs-id1167835345155\">\n<p id=\"fs-id1167835345157\"><strong>Solution</strong></p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>To find the \\(&nbsp;x&nbsp;\\)-intercept, let \\(&nbsp;y=0&nbsp;\\)</p>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>\\(&nbsp;2x+ 0 = 8&nbsp;\\)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>Solve for \\(&nbsp;x&nbsp;\\).</p>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>\\(&nbsp;x = 4&nbsp;\\)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>\\(&nbsp;x&nbsp;\\)-intercept</p>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>\\(&nbsp;(4, 0)&nbsp;\\)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>To find the \\(&nbsp;y&nbsp;\\)-intercept, let \\(&nbsp;x=0&nbsp;\\)</p>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>\\(&nbsp;2(0)+ y = 8&nbsp;\\)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>Solve for \\(&nbsp;y&nbsp;\\).</p>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>\\(&nbsp;y = 8&nbsp;\\)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>\\(&nbsp;y&nbsp;\\)-intercept</p>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>\\(&nbsp;(0, 8)&nbsp;\\)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table><br>\n</div>\n<div data-type=\"solution\" id=\"fs-id1167835345155\">\n<h4>Try It: Finding Intercepts from Graphs and Equations</h4>\n<div data-type=\"solution\" id=\"fs-id1167835345155\"><br></div>\n<div data-type=\"solution\" id=\"fs-id1167835345155\">Find the \\(&nbsp;x&nbsp;\\)- and \\(&nbsp;y&nbsp;\\)-intercept of \\(&nbsp;x+4y=8&nbsp;\\).</div>\n<div data-type=\"solution\" id=\"fs-id1167835345155\"><br></div>\n<div data-type=\"solution\" id=\"fs-id1167835345155\">Write down your answer, then select the <strong>Solution</strong> button to check your work.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow1\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n<!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n<!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-content\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"eventShow1\">\n<p id=\"fs-id1168345252532\">Here is how to find the intercepts.</p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>To find the x-intercept, let y=0</p>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>x+ 4(0) = 8</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>Solve for x.</p>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>x = 8</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>x-intercept</p>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>(8, 0)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>To find the y-intercept, let x=0</p>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>(0)+ 4y = 8</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>Solve for y.</p>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>y = 2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>y-intercept</p>\n</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">\n<p>(0, 2)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>How did you do? Know that you learn more from wrong answers than from right answers! Wrong answers help us find flaws in our thinking. Take a minute to think about why you got the question wrong. Then you won&rsquo;t get this type of question wrong again!<br></p>\n<section data-depth=\"1\" id=\"fs-id1170654942537\">\n</section>\n</div>"
